review_body:
Maybe I was too young to really enjoy 'First Blood' the way other people have. It's good, but the Rambo character is just a mess. Years later, in 'Rambo' (2008), he is fully developed, intelligent, and even profound at times. The effects were better, the pacing was better - as the years passed, Stallone learned how to make better movies with better characters.

'Rambo: Last Blood' (2019) feels more like a follow-up to 'Rambo' (2008) than the 5th movie in a franchise. I enjoyed the modernized plot and the 'old man Rambo' feel. He gets his *ss kicked early to add some realism to an overall unrealistic and over-the-top film. Despite the ridiculous final 20 minutes, I enjoyed it. This movie has everything you watch a Rambo movie to see. Solid effort.

